thub.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/5880.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/5880.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>Previously, running DataParallel in no_grad mode would change the<br>\nrequires_grad property of the network's parameters to False. The issue<br>\nis that Broadcast returns aliases of the inputs for the source device.<br>\nIn no_grad mode, it would deatch these inputs in-place.</p>\n<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #5851.\">Fixes</span> <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"306161171\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/5851\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/pytorch/pytorch/issues/5851/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/5851\">#5851</a></p>", "body_text": "Previously, running DataParallel in no_grad mode would change the\nrequires_grad property of the network's parameters to False. The issue\nis that Broadcast returns aliases of the inputs for the source device.\nIn no_grad mode, it would deatch these inputs in-place.\nFixes #5851", "body": "Previously, running DataParallel in no_grad mode would change the\r\nrequires_grad property of the network's parameters to False. The issue\r\nis that Broadcast returns aliases of the inputs for the source device.\r\nIn no_grad mode, it would deatch these inputs in-place.\r\n\r\nFixes #5851"}